Until I read what happened.  My guild entered the plane (at the time not breaking any rules because it was far enough away from the no mans time frame).  Fish checked half way through the raid and found out he was in violation.  He told Koi that he accepted sanctions, that he no longer uses his id.<br>
<br>
Him and Koi are friendly and do know each other.  He was not trying to start a dispute with her.  He feels that the calendar has out lived it's usefulness, and that if there are going to be any rules in place for the planes they need to change.  He says that all negotiations as to recreating rules for sharing the planes have come to an impasse in the guild leader forum.<br>
<br>
I am not officially speaking for my guild.  Just trying to make a short informative post.  If you want official post, check prexus.com for Dolphins couple of post he has put out there in response to the issues.<br>
<br>
I have friends in IV as well.  I hope they are just as friendly to me after this incident.  No I was not there.  I haven't logged in but twice in a month.  I will not debate the fcfs/calendar issues in public any more.  I feel it's a waste of time.  If any of my friends are reading this and they want to question me about it, be my guest.  I will tell you how I feel privately.  No I will not remove my Domus tag because of political issues on prexus.com that half the server are completely oblivious to.<br>
<br>
I belive that I treat people as individuals, weather they are in Stasis, or KTF or IV.  I understand that some don't want any thing to change as far as the current calendar rules.  That is their prerogative to try to keep the calendar in place, by sanctioning which ever guild breaks those agreements.<br>
<br>
I don't &quot;need&quot; (never said it wouldn't help me or be beneficial to me) a group, port, rez from IV members.  If an IV member that I do not know and have hardly any clue who they are decides they won't trade with me or grp with me or port me because of sanctions, it's really not going to bother me all that much.<br>
<br>
If Walker decides he want's nothing to do with me and doesn't want to be seen with me or wishes not to speak with me, because I have a Domus guild tag, it WILL upset me.  That goes for all of my friends in this guild.  But I doubt it will make me want to remove my guild tag.  I like that tag.  I like the things we do/have done together.  I like the sense of accomplishment that has come from learning on some very difficult raids with them.<br>
<br>
Not sure what I think about all this yet guys.  Some of you probably have read my comments on fcfs on prexus and know where I stand.  But I was never under the impression that the calendar would end because of Domus.<br>
<br>
