<br>
I know that our guild has all ways made midnight visits to the planes to get what we want.  And I don't ever remember breaking any rules.  Most of the members didn't bother to check scheduled times or the calendar rules.  They would leave that up to who ever was leading the raid and be content to follow for some midnight fun.<br>
<br>
Some have expressed their thoughts that they believed this practice was tacky.  But they didn't speak out about it much.  They knew that we were acting with in the rules and that to down us for our actions they would then have to try to change the rules.  Since the rules allowed for us to make midnight fcfs style raids in to the planes as long as we respected respawn times.<br>
<br>
All that has transpired so far is that Domus unintentionally broke the rules on one occasion, was called on it, accepted sanctions, and stated that said sanctions would not effect us since we have used the id once in 3 months or so.  For what ever reason (speculate all you want, she never names it) Koi stepped down as calendar moderator.  That's the full story.  And by the looks of the prexus.com board atm it would appear few even care about the issue any longer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/uballadragingboars.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balladragingboars</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Councilman</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/5/01 10:03:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stasis FCFS' KTF on TRAK</span><hr size=1> Its not tacky..if its not interfering with the next days raid, more often or not it does however, then people get pissy about it. After 2+ years people still dont know for sure the actual spawn time on the planes, well some dont. Which is why these fights happen. But Id be the first to hit Fear if the Shissar was up, if it didnt interfere with the next days raid.<br>
