BA <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/uhieya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hieya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/6/01 1:12:52 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.psylenced.freehomepage.com/Biopic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stasis FCFS' KTF on TRAK</span><hr size=1> On the sentiments posted above...<br>
<br>
I am now a member of Stasis. I didn't even have to apply. They just wanted me. If IV's members feel they dont want to rez, port, talk, sell, buy whatever from me anymore, thats their perogative. I tried my damnedest to join IV, it was ruined by 3 people. Actually mainly 1. I am tired of the hypocrisy going on with the BS politics occuring over FCFS vs. Calendar, and because of this I am now taking a stance for the system i prefer, one that i believe will keep this game interesting, and certainly more challenging. Koikeeper sees the flaws in the current system and she sees that compromise is more than likely not going to happen. Small guilds are strangling the system they cherish so much.<br>
<br>
I have helped IV out quite a bit since I first applied, asking for little or nothing in return. I've summoned your corpses, for free, rezzed you when clerics were not available, for free, and even helped you obtain a good deal of loots (granted this was returned in the same manner). Now I am being ridiculed by a select few of its members because of the things i did to help you. I won't state names, most of you know who they are anyhow from previous posts, and I wont kiss ass, cause im not that type of guy. I will stand up for what i believe in, and the friends i value, and I will publicly state when i feel someone has done something wrong (the domus issue, the charm issue, both of which my instincts turned out being correct after I had been flamed for doing it by IV), or when i have done something wrong and feel the need to apologize for it (the blanket statements i tend to make, and some of my obnoxious posts).<br>
<br>
Right now I feel backstabbed by IV, although only by the actions of a few select members. My definition of friendship transcends guild tags, and it will always be this way. Expect me to treat you no differently than you treat me. I just wanted to bid farewell to my friends who decide they nolonger want to interact with me anylonger, and say hello to those who define friendship in the same way that I do, and continue to be friends. I wish it had worked out, sincerely, but with FCFS more than likely rolling around, im jumping on the bandwagon now before i get steamrolled.<br>
<br>
Your friend,<br>
